<TEXT>Known as DJ Quentox (The OX that Rocks), Cook and DJ Baptiste started putting on youth club hip hop jams in Brighton, sowing the seeds of the city's flourishing hip hop scene today. These primitive 1980s block parties are recalled in the music documentary "South Coast", which documents Brighton's cult hip hop scene from its grass roots to the present day.
